  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Children and young people are moving less and less. In combination with an unhealthy diet,&#xD;
      this has led to a sharp increase in overweight and obesity among children worldwide. Very&#xD;
      often, physical illnesses occur in adolescence that can be directly attributed to the&#xD;
      overweight and obesity. In order to protect children from these consequences in time, a daily&#xD;
      exercise unit of 45 minutes is built into their learning. This exercise will take place in&#xD;
      addition to physical education classes as part of your child's school day and will be&#xD;
      conducted by a teacher. We will examine the children of the participating schools with regard&#xD;
      to health-related characteristics.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
